Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.26,0:00:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been a physician and a psychiatrist for 35 years.\NI've worked in the field of psychoanalysis and psychotherapy and group therapy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,psychodynamics of the various schools.\NI've done a lot of research on nutrition and its relationship to brain chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and its relationship to mental illness and emotions.\NFor the last 10 years, I've been doing research into the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the applications of that knowledge that came out of that research\Nto an understanding of that field of knowledge which the world calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.93,0:00:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, inherent in what we're talking about today\Nis that relationship between body, mind, and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.59,0:00:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does that really mean?\NIs that something scientific that we can clinically verify?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.93,0:01:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is that some kind of a New Age fantasy?\NOur talk for today will be about the prevention of stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.14,0:01:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress.\NStress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A subject about which we read so much.\NIts implications for health.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.30,0:01:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Its implications for emotional and psychological health.\NIts meaning in industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.28,0:01:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Its meaning in business.\NThe realization now of wide areas in our culture
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.30,0:01:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of being aware of what stress means,\Nwhat's implied in this disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.91,0:01:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so today we will need to look closely at what this relationship is\Nbetween the body and its response to stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.63,0:01:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind and how this relates to spirit.\NSo we'll be covering today how stress results from a point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It results from what we are holding in mind.\NFrom our attitudes and our beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.92,0:01:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll see that the source of stress is within ourselves.\NIt's really not in the world at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.64,0:02:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as escaping stress\Nbecause its source, its cause, is within us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.76,0:02:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Its source.\NIts source is not within the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.00,0:02:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll be reversing the way the mind usually looks at things\Nabout cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.82,0:02:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see that cause is not in the world\Nand effect in mind, but vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That the level of power, the level of cause,\Nis held in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.58,0:02:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And this brings about our experiences of what happens in the world.\NOur folklore intuitively knows this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.62,0:02:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because it says,\None man's meat is another man's poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.48,0:02:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One man's meat is another man's poison.\NAnd in that we have the secret of what we're looking at today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.14,0:02:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The power is not in the event.\NThe power is not something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.86,0:02:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of creating our experience\Nof all events in life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.80,0:02:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lie within us.\NAnd it's by reowning our power then
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.92,0:03:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can learn how to prevent stress.\NSo we will be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.18,0:03:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,methods of precluding stress\Ninstead of treating its aftermath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.18,0:03:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The so-called stress reduction programs\Nwhich are so commonly available in our society today
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are really methods of handling\Nthe effects of stress once it's already happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.18,0:03:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The relaxation programs\Nto relieve the tension within the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say,\Nthe horse is already out of the barn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be looking at ways\Nto offset this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.14,0:03:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the tension never arises in the body.\NThese various ways of handling stress
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.14,0:03:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the medical model.\NI recently got a brochure, in fact this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.17,0:03:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It says stress and heart disease.\NStress and heart disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And right there we have a whole program.\NWe have a whole program which the mind has bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:04:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That stress is something out there.\NStress is something inherent in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.17,0:04:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That the result of stress,\Nis going to affect the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.17,0:04:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart with all its symbolic meaning to us.\NThe various papers then had to do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,really with heart disease.\NThe consequence of stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming about through our levels of consciousness\Nand manifesting within the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.06,0:04:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all things are experienced\Nwithin consciousness then today,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.86,0:04:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be looking at that relationship\Nbetween body, mind and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.86,0:04:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this talk, as we have in other talks,\Nwe want to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and carefully define\Nthings that you can verify
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.86,0:04:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,through your own experience.\NAnd in this talk as well as the other talks
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.86,0:04:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be talking about\Nclinical verifiable experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.86,0:04:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from the viewpoint of the skeptical scientist\Nwho believes only what can be clinically repeated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.86,0:05:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and which he can verify through his own inner experience.\NAnd so we invite you during this talk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out within yourself\Nthe truth of all that we are talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with we notice that\Nthe body itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a characteristic of the body,\Nis that it is insentient.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, the body has no capacity\Nto experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.44,0:05:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean by that?\NI mean that the arm in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.44,0:05:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot experience its own existence.\NIt cannot experience its own armness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot experience that it is\Nmuch less where it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.44,0:05:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or how big it is,\Nor what it's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know what's going on with the body?\NWe know because of the senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't experience the body,\Nwe experience the senses reporting this of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.04,0:05:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The senses themselves have no capacity\Nto experience themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:06:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,An ear, the vibrations going through the eighth nerve,\Nvibrating the tympanic membrane, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has no way to experience itself.\NWhere does experience of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,take place?\NIt takes place in something greater than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we call mind.\NIt's because of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So all experience of the body is occurring\Nin an energy field, in a level,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that we call mind.\NMind itself, very curiously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.06,0:06:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,has no capacity to experience itself.\NAn amazing thought until you look into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that a thought,\Nof and by itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,has no capacity to experience its own thoughtness.\NA memory has no capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.45,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself\Nto experience its own memoryness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A fantasy about the future\Nhas no capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.45,0:06:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Our imagination, our emotions,\Nall that goes on in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.45,0:06:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is only experienced\Nbecause of a greater and larger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.45,0:06:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field than mind,\Nand that is what we call consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.45,0:07:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field more diffuse\Nand formless,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.45,0:07:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,capable of experiencing change,\Ncapable of experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.45,0:07:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,any phenomena.\NIt is because of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're aware\Nof what is going on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of mind\Nwe're aware of what is going on with sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.12,0:07:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of sensations\Nwe're aware of what goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the physical body.\NCuriously enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.63,0:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,even consciousness itself\Ncannot report what is going on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,within itself\Nexcept for a field which is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.63,0:07:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and without dimension\Nand called the absolute knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.63,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or awareness.\NIt is because of awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.63,0:07:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it is because of that quality\Nof awareness which goes with our existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes with our beingness.\NIt's because we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.63,0:07:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we're capable of awareness.\NOut of awareness then comes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.63,0:07:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness of what goes on\Nwithin consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.63,0:08:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness reporting to us\Nwhat is going on within mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.63,0:08:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind reporting what goes on\Nwith sensations about the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.63,0:08:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we can see\Nthat that which we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when we say I or me\Nin its highest and greatest sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about the capacity\Nfor awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is on this energy field,\Nin this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and level of consciousness\Nthat we'll be talking today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is within consciousness itself\Nthat all experience is being experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.66,0:08:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thereby to address ourselves directly\Nto the source and the place
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experience\Nwill bring us to the capabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of precluding the sources of stress.\NIn doing this we'll be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.20,0:08:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a map of consciousness\Nwhich we've referred to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.20,0:08:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in these other talks.\NIt's a mathematical model.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.20,0:08:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Not purely mathematical\Nbut it is based upon energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.20,0:09:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness\Nand these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.20,0:09:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have been calibrated\Nas to their relative power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the energy fields\Nhere which are labeled
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.74,0:09:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,according to common human experience.\NEasily understood
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you look at it\Nyou will find that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easily understandable.\NAt the very bottom for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.74,0:09:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we have guilt\Nwhich is in its form of self-hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a destructive negative emotion.\NWe know that from guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.16,0:09:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is seen\Nas a place of suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Guiltiness has an energy field of 30.\NThese are states that come close to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Death we calibrate at zero.\NIf we start with death at zero
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.16,0:09:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,then to be of a very high consciousness\Nto become enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates out at 600.\NGuilt you'll see in apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and grief and fear\Nand desire and anger and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.77,0:09:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All these negative energy fields\Nall have a negative
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.77,0:10:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or a destructive direction.\NYou'll notice that their calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are low in number.\NFor instance apathy at 50
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.77,0:10:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has half the power of fear\Nwhich calibrates out at 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.77,0:10:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear at 100 has half the energy of courage\Nwhich calibrates out at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.77,0:10:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Desire has half the energy\Nof that state called neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.77,0:10:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or being detached.\NSo we can calibrate the energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.77,0:10:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and these can be reduplicated by anybody\Nusing very common techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.77,0:10:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance kinesiology.\NAnybody in their own home can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.77,0:10:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,verify themselves\Nthe relative energies
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.77,0:10:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the directions of the field.\NThese fields which go to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.77,0:10:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you hold in mind\Na thought which is angry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.77,0:10:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a thought about something you regret\Nsomething you are sad about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or something you fear\Nand if you press down on the person's arm
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.77,0:10:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see they instantly go weak.\NThe cerebral hemispheres become desynchronized
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.77,0:11:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the acupuncture energy system\Ngoes out of kilt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.77,0:11:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person instantly goes to sleep.\NThe person instantly loses their power
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and their energy.\NIf we go above the level of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll see the energy field now\Nwhich was in this direction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.77,0:11:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,now goes neutral\Nthe needle swings to the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.77,0:11:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,By telling the truth\Nby telling the truth about things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by moving towards that which is true\Nthe energy field now swings to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,into that which is positive.\NThat which is positive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which supports and reinforces life\Nthat energy of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.77,0:11:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It is aligned with the truth.\NAnd so the great beings of great wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.77,0:11:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who have walked this earth\Nwhen we calibrate their energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.77,0:11:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,they run up into the 600s\Nand the great avatars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.77,0:11:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the great saviors of mankind\Ntheir energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.77,0:11:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,run from the 700s on up into infinity.\NSo you might say the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.90,0:12:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,begins at this energy field of 200\Nand expands ever upward
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.90,0:12:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,into an ever increasing lovingness\Nalignment with truth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.90,0:12:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and health follows the same pattern.\NThe farther we go up in our energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.90,0:12:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the more automatic becomes the health\Nuntil finally there is a joy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the aliveness\Nthe exquisite pleasure of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which automatically becomes healthy\Nand it automatically heals its own diseases
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because at an energy field of about 540\Nwhich is the energy field of healing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,healing automatically\Nbegins to take place in the body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.93,0:12:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at an energy field of 540.\NSo as we talk about stress
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.60,0:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's obvious that we're going to be\Nlooking at these conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,these pre-existing conditions\Nwithin the consciousness of the person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.60,0:12:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which set the person up\Nto experience life in a stressful way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:13:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that a person\Nwho is identified with this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.60,0:13:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to experience a world\Nwhich is going to make them feel constantly guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that a person who identifies\Non this energy field here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.98,0:13:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,one of hopelessness and despair\Nis going to experience the world as hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of life's experiences\Nare going to be colored by that expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up to grief\Nwe'll see that the person who is full of regret
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.18,0:13:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and concern with loss in the past\Nis going to see this as a sad world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.18,0:13:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there is a God\NHe would be a God who doesn't love you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.18,0:13:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn't care for you\Nand ignores you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up to the energy field of fear\Nwe see that coming out of the suppressed energy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.21,0:13:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which has been held throughout life\Nheld unconsciously
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.21,0:13:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of fearfulness\Nthe preoccupation with anxiety about the future
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:14:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who is constantly worrying\Nthe world looks to that person
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.21,0:14:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,like a frightening place.\NThe God of such a world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.21,0:14:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,would then be punitive.\NAnd so therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.46,0:14:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all that person's experience now\Nis coming forth in the form of fright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.46,0:14:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is always wanting\Nexperiences this as a frustrating world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The angry person\Nis always running into conflict and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The prideful person\Nis always experiencing challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.46,0:14:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore assumes a defensive posture.\NSo that's just a brief look at
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be coming back to this map of consciousness\Nin greater detail
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.46,0:14:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how it operates\Nin the automatic setting up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and setting us up for stress.\NWe begin to suspect now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.75,0:14:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from that statement\Nthat one man's meat is another man's poison
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that the setup for stress then\Nis coming out of our own values.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.75,0:14:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out of our own position about life.\NIt's coming out of the programs
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.75,0:15:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're holding operative\Nwithin our own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to look now\Nfor the source of stress
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the world\Nbut in what is it we are holding in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.75,0:15:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that assigns to a given event\Nthe experience of it as stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.68,0:15:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In looking at this\Nwe'll look now at some attitudes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.68,0:15:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,some ways of being with life\Nthat set us up for this kind of an experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll cite some examples\Nwhich are available to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.78,0:15:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I had an in-law\Nfor instance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who used to come out\Nand visit my house in the country
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time I lived in the middle\Nof a hundred acres of woods
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.78,0:15:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thirty miles from New York City.\NAnd there there was only stillness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.35,0:15:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact the only thing you could hear\Nwas the rustling of the leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.35,0:15:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the song of the birds.\NAnd she was a somewhat elderly lady
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and she'd lived most of her life\Nin New York City
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.35,0:16:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know on East 28th Street\Naround that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And she would hate to come out to the house\Nand when she had to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.86,0:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she would stay as briefly as possible.\NIn fact two or three days
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was all she could stand.\NAnd the peace and the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,drove her crazy.\NAnd she just couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.86,0:16:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And she couldn't wait to get back to the city\Nwhere she would sigh with relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And her apartment in the city\Nyou know faced the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.86,0:16:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And so from her open window\Nshe could talk to everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she could hear the hustle and bustle of the city.\NAnd she felt secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the midst of\Nyou know it was mugger land
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.86,0:16:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lower East Side, etc.\Nall those areas of the city at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.86,0:16:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,were ripe with muggings.\NSo here she was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you know in a situation\Nwhich another person might consider as stressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people might\Nconsider that part of the city scary indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So what she experienced as security\Nbeing there in the throngs of people
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sound of the garbage cans in the morning\Nand the garbage trucks
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,making their racket at 5 a.m.\Nto her was reassurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.86,0:17:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Being safe and secure\Nin the middle of 100 acres of woods
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.86,0:17:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to her was a threat.\NWe look at the interesting experience then
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of Devil's Island\Nthe French penal colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.89,0:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course this is well documented\Nthat when the French government
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.89,0:17:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,out of protest\Ncoming from the humanism movement
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.89,0:17:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of social protest\Nclosed this disgraceful colony
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.92,0:17:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened was that\Nthey allowed the prisoners
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to go loose on the island.\NThey released them from these animal cages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Torture cages is what they really were.\NAnd so the prisoners were now allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.92,0:17:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the freedom of the island.\NThe freedom to walk around at will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.92,0:17:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what did the prisoners do?\NMuch to the surprise of the authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the prisoners had been in these cells for many years\Nat night they went back to their prison cells to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.92,0:18:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They felt frightened and lonely and insecure\Neven though for the first time in all these years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.11,0:18:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they had the freedom which they so ostensibly\Nhad cried for and demanded over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.11,0:18:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of security then came from\Nthe feeling of being back in the jail cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.11,0:18:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So to some of us a jail cell would be\Nthe maximum threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.11,0:18:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, no greater horror could befall us.\NAnd what have other people done in a prison cell?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.11,0:18:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They've written prize winning novels.\NThey've written staggering pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of literature.\NThings written in jail cells and prisons
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.11,0:18:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,have changed the course and the history of mankind\Nfor better or for worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.11,0:18:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler after all wrote Mein Kampf\Nwhile in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.11,0:18:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Another interesting example\Nin contrast to Devil's Island
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.11,0:18:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is exemplified by the movie Lost Horizon.\NYou'll remember in that movie
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:19:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which I remember well from childhood\NI saw it a number of times
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.14,0:19:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ronald Coleman.\NThe other passengers of the plane
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.14,0:19:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know land in the Himalayas\Nand they go through a pass
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.14,0:19:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and they come into Shangri-La\Nwhich represents a heavenly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.14,0:19:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,almost a heavenly condition.\NIts energy field is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.14,0:19:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably up in the 600s.\NA place of unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.14,0:19:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of unending bliss.\NAnd although Ronald Coleman was ready
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the experience and himself benefited God\Ngreatly and expanded his own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.59,0:19:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the other members of the passengers\Ntook it in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.59,0:19:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was interesting to watch of six different people\Nthe six different reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.59,0:19:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of them weren't quite ready\Nfor the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.59,0:19:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Experienced it as sort of stress\Ndue to its newness and its strangeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:20:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They felt stressed for a while\Nbut then adjusted to it and accepted
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.46,0:20:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a heavenly condition in their life.\NBut several of the people were acutely
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.46,0:20:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,disturbed by it.\NRemember the person who played
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.46,0:20:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ronald Coleman's brother in the movie\Nbecame almost paranoid and agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Demanded to return to the real world.\NAnd a person who was stranded there
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.46,0:20:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from a previous plane accident\Nby that time had actually become paranoid
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.46,0:20:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,delusional and psychotic.\NAnd so how it was experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.46,0:20:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by these different people then\Nrepresented not a reaction to where
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.46,0:20:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they were but a reaction to their own position.\NAnd what they were talking about then
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,was not what's out there\Nbut their own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.46,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one time I was flying out of Ecuador\Nand at that time there were only two planes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a week going out of Ecuador.\NAnd so I got there for the Thursday plane
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.42,0:21:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course I had reservations\Nmany months in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.42,0:21:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When I got there the first thing they told me\Nwas that my name wasn't on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.42,0:21:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing they said was that\Nthe plane was not leaving on Thursday this week anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't leaving until Saturday.\NWell, for some reason it just seemed to be humorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.02,0:21:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed to be hilarious.\NSomehow when you're in Ecuador
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.02,0:21:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at 10,000 feet altitude and above\Nthe fact that the plane is going to be late
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.02,0:21:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in three days just doesn't mean a thing.\NNobody got upset about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.02,0:21:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the interesting thing about the clock\Nin the airport which hung in the middle of the ceiling
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.57,0:21:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was that the clock had stopped many years ago\Nand nobody had even bothered to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.57,0:21:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the expectation then\Nwhat is stressful coming out of this attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.57,0:21:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we had an easy going social attitude\Nin which precision within the material world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.57,0:21:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't considered to be important.\NHuman values were of greater importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:22:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And because human values\Nbecause of the convenience of the crew, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.57,0:22:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that was more important.\NAnd so nobody seemed to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.57,0:22:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If that had happened in a different social setting\NLaGuardia airport let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.57,0:22:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that your Thursday plane is not leaving until Saturday\Nyou would have experienced it as stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.57,0:22:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the set and the setting, the expectation\Nthe cultural attitude that you buy into.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.57,0:22:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In a different culture we buy a different attitude\Nand in that culture
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.57,0:22:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this event was not even experienced as stressful.\NAs a matter of fact
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.70,0:22:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when I got there for the Saturday noon plane\Nit was due to leave at quarter to twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There was some kind of delay.\NIt was the only plane on the runway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.70,0:22:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the plane sat there\Nand then suddenly it was twelve o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.70,0:22:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At twelve o'clock they shut down for siesta.\NSo not only did the Thursday plane not leave until Saturday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.70,0:22:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it didn't leave at quarter to twelve\Nit left at three o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:23:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the plane sat there\Nwhile everybody took a siesta.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.70,0:23:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When the siesta was over\Neverybody gathered their stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.70,0:23:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,got on the plane and away we went.\NNobody upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody sort of totally relaxed at ease\Nat peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be at peace\Nwith a three day delay in your plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.73,0:23:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So within these experiences that we have cited\Nis the key
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.73,0:23:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the key to the understanding of stress.\NBecause when we talk about stress
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.73,0:23:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're really talking about then\Nis the experience of what is stressful within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.73,0:23:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To consider the body\Nas part of a stress response
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.73,0:23:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very late reaction.\NThe body is only responding
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.30,0:23:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to what is held in mind.\NThe body is only responding to that which is held in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.30,0:23:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And so by altering what we hold in mind\Nour expectations, our way of being with life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.30,0:23:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we can preclude the development of stress.\NI didn't have to go to a relaxation program
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.30,0:24:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle the stress\Nof the plane being three days late.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.30,0:24:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have to go to some kind of\Ncoronary exercise program
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.30,0:24:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect my heart from stress.\NThere wasn't any stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.30,0:24:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the real approach to stress then\Nis to prevent it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.30,0:24:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To preclude it.\NTo understand how it arises
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.30,0:24:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and where it arises.\NSo our first understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.30,0:24:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think it's rather obvious by now\Nfrom the examples we've given
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.69,0:24:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the source of what we experience as stress\Nis within ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.69,0:24:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not exist in the world.\NIt doesn't exist in plane schedules.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.69,0:24:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in prison cells.\NNowhere does it exist
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.69,0:24:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,except within our own consciousness.\NAnd so we need to go back then to this map
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.69,0:24:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to this field of consciousness\Nand understand it a little bit more closely
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.69,0:24:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and then our awareness of this subject\Nwill advance rather rapidly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.69,0:24:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because what we're talking about\Nis really easy to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.69,0:25:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something you really know already.\NIt's just that we're going to bring it into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.23,0:25:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that these energy fields\Non the bottom which are
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.23,0:25:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say adverse to life\Ndestructive of life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.23,0:25:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we would call them stress\Njust by their own nature
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.23,0:25:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy field indicates a stressful direction.\NThat we move above it to neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.23,0:25:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we move in a positive direction\Nto that which is unstressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.23,0:25:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that Shangri-La would be up here.\NAll things are experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.23,0:25:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in their beauty and perfection\Nthe oneness of life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.23,0:25:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconditional love\Nand the lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.23,0:25:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of these energy fields\Nout of these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.74,0:25:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,which are calibrated as to their relative power\Nto the right of it we see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.74,0:25:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotions that come out of that position\Nthat way of being with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.74,0:25:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that those who are prone to guiltiness\Nfor instance
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.74,0:25:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotion is one of self-hatred.\NThe experience of life is that it is destructive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.74,0:26:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we said\Nwhat they see is a world of suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.74,0:26:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They see a world of suffering.\NThe person who is holding this position
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.84,0:26:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of apathy about life\Nthe emotion is one of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.84,0:26:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is hopeless.\NLife is despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.84,0:26:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a loss of energy.\NThe world is seen as hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.84,0:26:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the god of such a world is dead.\NIf we move out of apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.58,0:26:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if we pour enough energy into a person in apathy\Nwe can get them up to grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.58,0:26:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief is a state in which you can express emotion.\NIt has a certain biologic purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.58,0:26:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression of grief\Nlike the crying of the child brings the mother
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.58,0:26:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,has a certain biologic purpose.\NThose who are in that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.58,0:26:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,are looking to the past\Nand they see their life
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.58,0:26:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,filled with regret and loss.\NThey become dispirited.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.58,0:27:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience this as a sad world\Nand the god of that world ignores you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.58,0:27:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that the person who is coming from\Nthe suppressed energy field of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.58,0:27:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking to life\Nfilled with worry and anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.58,0:27:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience life as frightening.\NNow what is life?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.18,0:27:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a view of the world.\NThe view of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.18,0:27:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?\NWhat is the thing in and of itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.18,0:27:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it coming out of the event?\NWe see then that these fields of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.18,0:27:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are really portholes.\NThey are ways in which we see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.18,0:27:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the color of the glasses that we put on.\NIf we put on gray glasses coming out of grief
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.18,0:27:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,everything looks sad.\NA person walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.73,0:27:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,who is coming from this energy field\Nsees everything on the street as hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.73,0:27:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at man and man's conditions.\NHe opens the paper and he sees hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.73,0:27:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's condition is hopeless.\NAs he walks down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.73,0:28:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he looks at the old people\Nand he sees how hopeless their condition is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.73,0:28:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at the children\Nand he sees how hopeless it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.73,0:28:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are going to have to grow up\Nin a world of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.73,0:28:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is sad\Nwalks down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.73,0:28:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and they literally experience\Ntheir perception is one of sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.73,0:28:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When they open the newspaper\Nthey see all that there is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.73,0:28:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to be sad about in the world.\NAs they walk down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.73,0:28:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the sadness of man's condition.\NThey see the trash on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.73,0:28:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They look at the old people\Nand they think how sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.73,0:28:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,how sad aging is.\NThey look at the children
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.73,0:28:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and they feel sorry for them.\NThey think how sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.73,0:28:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They pity the children,\Nthe kind of a world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.73,0:28:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they are going to have to grow up in.\NYou know the pain of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.73,0:28:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are holding so much pain\Nthat the pity expresses itself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.73,0:28:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How sad for these children.\NThe person who is coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.53,0:28:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of fear\Nsees and experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.53,0:28:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and creates in his world\Nthe experience of that which is fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.53,0:29:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person opens the newspaper.\NHe reads the same newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.53,0:29:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sees how fearful this world is.\NKillings and murder
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.53,0:29:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and muggings and war and bombings.\NHe walks down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.17,0:29:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sees how frightening is the world.\NHe sees the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.17,0:29:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the chance for accidents.\NHe sees people can twist their
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.17,0:29:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,ankle on the curb.\NThere should be warning signs all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.17,0:29:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who sees this\Nas a frightening world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.17,0:29:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,double locks everything.\NYou know I know people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.17,0:29:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who double lock their car\Nwithin their own double lock garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.17,0:29:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,within their own double lock yard\Nin an area which has never had a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.17,0:29:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the fear then is coming from within\Nand it projects onto the world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.46,0:29:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a frightening appearance.\NIf you have got fear colored glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.46,0:29:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,everything looks like fear.\NAnd if you search for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.46,0:29:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you would see a fearful God, you know.\NThe God of a frightening world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.46,0:30:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is someone to be afraid of.\NThe person who moves up in the street
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.19,0:30:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,into a higher energy field\Nof desiringness and wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.19,0:30:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,often this comes about merely by education.\NLet's say people at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.19,0:30:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,into hopelessness through television,\Nthe whole third world,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.19,0:30:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,segments of the lowest socioeconomic groups\Nin our society in the last 20 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.19,0:30:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or 30 years.\NWhen television came along,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.19,0:30:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,began to see that which other people have.\NWhat came up out of that was desire, desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.38,0:30:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is felt in the emotional field then,\Nas wanting and craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.38,0:30:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This expresses itself in its fullest\Nin the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.38,0:30:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The process going on in consciousness\Nis one of entrapment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.38,0:30:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you desire something,\Nyou begin to want it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.38,0:30:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you then experience this world as frustrating.\NSo the stress then that this person experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.38,0:30:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the endless frustration\Nbecause coming out of that sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.38,0:31:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,solar plexus endless wantingness,\Nit's the person who is never satisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.38,0:31:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what they get.\NThey're always wanting something more.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.38,0:31:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If they get you to concede to their wishes,\Nthey bring up more wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.38,0:31:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like it's an endless control\Nthat they want over life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.38,0:31:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They see this as a very frustrating world\Nand so as they walk down the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.38,0:31:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they see all the things they want.\NThey see the cars that they want,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.38,0:31:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the kind of appearance,\Nthey see the appurtenances that they want,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.38,0:31:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the addresses that they want.\NAs they open the newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.38,0:31:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they're seeing all the things that they want.\NThey want to change the world they want to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.38,0:31:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So this endless addiction to getting this\Nthen creates an endless stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.74,0:31:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This stress, as you see,\Nis coming from within the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.74,0:31:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no refusal on the part of the world\Nto come to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.74,0:31:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your endless desiringness for it.\NThe person who, out of this frustration then,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.44,0:32:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,moves up to anger,\Nbegins to experience this as an angry world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.44,0:32:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They're full of resentment,\Nthey're boiling over with hate and grievance.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.44,0:32:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens with a person like this\Nis the suppressed energy now of the angriness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.44,0:32:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is ready to spill forth in any event.\NThey see this world as competitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.44,0:32:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So to this person,\Nbecause of the kind of glasses they're wearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.44,0:32:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they're wearing angry glasses,\Nwhen they open the newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.54,0:32:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,their stomach churns with wrath and indignation\Nand anger over the events that they're reading about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.54,0:32:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As they walk down the street,\Nthey see many things to be angry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.70,0:32:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All the conditions,\Nthe conditions of the street signs,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.70,0:32:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the conditions of the street,\Nthe newspapers there on the street now make them angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.70,0:32:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They look at the children, that makes them angry.\NThey look at the old folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.70,0:32:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They think of their conditions and they become angry.\NSo they live in a world of injustice,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.70,0:32:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,indignation,\Na competitive world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.70,0:33:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if they have a used car lot,\Nyou know, sell used cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.70,0:33:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody else opens another used car lot down the street,\Nthey consider this competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.70,0:33:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They look at it like lose,\Nthey're going to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.70,0:33:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because these people live in a win-lose world.\NTherefore, the stomach is always tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.70,0:33:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't moved up to a higher level of harmony and cooperation.\NConsequently, they don't realize
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.86,0:33:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that the more used car lots on the street,\Nthe better for business.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.86,0:33:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They would see it as competition.\NSo the world becomes a threatening place.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.86,0:33:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The god of that kind of a universe\Nwould be the god of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.02,0:33:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of this angriness,\Nthese are warlike people ready for combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.02,0:33:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a chip on their shoulder.\NThat anger is ready to burst forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.69,0:33:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is very stressful then.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.69,0:33:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the suppressed anger.\NSo somebody should back into their fender in the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.69,0:33:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Up comes the anger.\NUp comes the cursing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.69,0:34:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Up comes the threat of the lawsuit,\Nthe angriness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.69,0:34:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person can move up to pride,\Nand there's a lot of energy in pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.88,0:34:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you see these are all negative destructive emotions.\NPride, although we like to think of it as constructive,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.88,0:34:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in essence it is really destructive.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.88,0:34:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because pride is denial.\NIts expression is really one of arrogance and contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.88,0:34:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And because the process going on in consciousness\Nis one of inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.88,0:34:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The prideful person then becomes very polarized in his positions.\NHe's prideful like the angry person.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.88,0:34:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,His position is right and they live in a world of right and wrong.\NIt's a world of win-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.88,0:34:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore there is always a stress going on within that person\Nbecause they see all relationships and interactions and transactions
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.88,0:34:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of win-lose.\NAnd the win-lose is about status.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.88,0:34:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with\Nownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.88,0:35:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that person, when he reads the newspaper,\Nis seeing the status of all that is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.23,0:35:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The status of the people that is being written about.\NWhen he walks down the street, he sees nothing but symbols of status.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.23,0:35:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The labels on clothes,\Nthe addresses,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.23,0:35:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things about life now become status.\NAnd they're very interested in who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.23,0:35:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from a status viewpoint.\NThese are all vulnerable positions as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.23,0:35:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all positions\Nof victim really
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.23,0:35:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of these positions below the level of truth\Nproject the source of happiness as outside yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.23,0:35:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives your power away.\NIt says the source of meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.23,0:35:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of happiness,\Nthe source of value is something outside myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.23,0:35:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somewhere out there.\NIt's coming from lack because it's saying if it's out there
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.23,0:35:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's something I have to get.\NIf it's something I have to get it means I lack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.23,0:36:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It means something could stand in my way.\NAnd so to live in that kind of a world is to always live in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.23,0:36:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Always live under threat\Nbecause something outside of yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.23,0:36:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be blocked from it.\NIt can be taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of victimhood.\NVictimhood because we've given away our power to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.23,0:36:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We say that the source of happiness is out there.\NThe source of stress is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.36,0:36:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no hope for relieving stress by changing the world.\NWhy is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.36,0:36:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because stress doesn't exist in the world.\NStress is an inexperience within consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.36,0:36:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can change the world to relieve stress.\NWhat can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.71,0:36:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We can own, begin to own the truth about it,\Nto have the courage to look at the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.71,0:36:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute we do that we change the energy field.\NWe see that the needle now goes to neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.71,0:36:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're coming out of destructive on our way into positive.\NWhen we're willing to face something,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.35,0:36:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,face the facts,\Nto face, cope and handle it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.35,0:37:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is we become re-empowered.\NThat means we begin to own back the power to ourself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.35,0:37:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're coming closer to the truth.\NAnd a prisoner who's on the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.96,0:37:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of a world does that person see?\NThey see a world of challenge, of growth and of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.96,0:37:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,An exciting, fun world.\NA place where you're glad to be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.96,0:37:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that same person opens the newspaper\Nand he sees all the tremendous opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.96,0:37:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for man to move into and solve and resolve this problem.\NAnd he has all kinds of problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.96,0:37:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, solving things in his own mind.\NHe just wishes he could try.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.96,0:37:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So it becomes an exciting world then of opportunity and growth,\Nwhich he begins to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.96,0:37:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where can I fit in?\NWhere can I start expressing myself
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.96,0:37:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and experiencing some of these opportunities?\NThe kind of a God that he experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.96,0:37:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of this world of opportunity\Nis a God of open-mindedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.96,0:38:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the open mind now begins to change,\Nobviously, that which is stressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.96,0:38:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is stressful down here\Nbecomes perhaps an object of curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.96,0:38:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and an opportunity for growth to a person here.\NMoving up to the next energy field we call neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.57,0:38:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,where the energy calibrates out at 250.\NLook how much more power we have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.57,0:38:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,than these positions up down below.\NNot only more power, but we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.57,0:38:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that power is now being used in a constructive,\Npositive direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.57,0:38:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though down here our antenna\Nis tuned to the negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.57,0:38:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it's turned to neutral.\NNow we're tuning our antenna to the positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.57,0:38:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to experience life in a positive direction\Nbecause we are the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.57,0:38:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer is not out there.\NIt is within our own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.57,0:38:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That person is willing to let go\Na lot of their positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.57,0:38:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the positions that make this person\Nand person's life hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.57,0:38:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of being always defensive\Ndue to his pridefulness, his importance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.57,0:39:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of always being right,\Nthe position of either the atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.57,0:39:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or the bigot or the zealot\Nthat leads to all the religious wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.57,0:39:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, my position is right,\Ntherefore your position is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.14,0:39:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to let that go,\Nthe person becomes somewhat unattached.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.14,0:39:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They begin to transcend their vulnerability to the world.\NThe process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.14,0:39:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they're released.\NThe world begins to look
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.14,0:39:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,okay to them.\NThe god of such a world now
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.14,0:39:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is the god of freedom.\NHow is that okayness expressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.27,0:39:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a person on this level,\Non the way to a job interview,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.27,0:39:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would say, you know, if I get this job\Nit'll be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.27,0:39:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't, that's okay too\Nbecause there's other job opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.27,0:39:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I would really like to look at.\NAnd so he's not stuck, he hasn't put his
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.27,0:39:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,survival on any one particular thing.\NBeginning to own
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.27,0:39:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power is within myself.\NAs we move into willingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.27,0:40:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we add something else now\Nfrom the process of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.27,0:40:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We add intention.\NIt means a yes-ness, a joining,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.27,0:40:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an alignment, an agreement with life.\NAnd such a person
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.43,0:40:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to see the world\Nas friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.43,0:40:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So when these people walk down the street,\Nthe god of that kind of a world
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.43,0:40:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,would become promising and hopeful.\NTheir experience now
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.43,0:40:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the newspaper\Nis they begin to open it up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.43,0:40:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and they see all the evidences\Nof man's cooperation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.43,0:40:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,man's struggle to solve its own problems.\NThey see what this person sees as destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.43,0:40:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as merely the process,\Nthe working out of the balance of forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.43,0:40:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They begin to see\Na friendlier world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.43,0:40:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when they walk down the street\Nthey see a friendly look.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.43,0:40:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You see their perception has changed.\NThey see the friendliness of old people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.43,0:40:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Old people who no longer have to make it\Nin the world, you know, very often
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.43,0:40:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,are much more open to be friendly.\NSimple to walk up to most older people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.43,0:41:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and strike up a conversation instantly.\NThey don't look at you with that paranoid distrust
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.43,0:41:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,or size you up and down to see where you stand\Nin a competitive, prideful world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.43,0:41:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They begin to see\Nthe old people as friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.85,0:41:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They see the friendliness of the young children.\NThey become conscious of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.85,0:41:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that children are friendly.\NIt's easy to strike up a relationship with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.01,0:41:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so moving up\Ninto acceptance then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.01,0:41:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you really begin to accept that one\Nis the source of one's own experience of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.01,0:41:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've said in other talks,\Na person who's reached
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.01,0:41:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,this level of awareness,\Nwho's owned the power back over his own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.01,0:41:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,realizes that no matter where you put him,\Nhe's going to somehow make do.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.01,0:41:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You put him on a desert island,\Nyou come back a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.01,0:41:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know he's carving coconuts,\Nand he's got a tree house.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.04,0:41:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You put him in a jail cell,\Nhe'll write a novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.04,0:41:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or he'll sit cross-legged and go into meditation,\Nor he'll become a jailhouse lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.04,0:41:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and get a law degree.\NThe power to create
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.04,0:42:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,my experience of life is within me.\NThe person has re-owned
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.04,0:42:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,their own power.\NConsequently, such a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.04,0:42:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of that kind of a world\Nand universe of experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.04,0:42:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes not only promising and hopeful,\Nbut merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.04,0:42:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A merciful God no longer to be feared.\NThat person is adequate and confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.04,0:42:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We want that kind of a person\Nto go out after the big contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.04,0:42:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that person is able to accept\Nthe upside and the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.04,0:42:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the realities of life\Nand can accept their own limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.04,0:42:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, a person coming out of pride\Ncan't accept that they are limited
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.04,0:42:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have to come from a prideful,\Nmacho position.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.42,0:42:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in acceptance,\Nwhen the company says,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.42,0:42:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd like you to go to Venezuela\Nand close such and such a deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.58,0:42:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a person who is adequate and confident\Ncould say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.58,0:42:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get along with that company\Nand I don't get along with that particular man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.58,0:42:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I do much better in Belgium.\NYou know, I can sell twice as much in Belgium.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.58,0:43:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you let Jim go down to Venezuela?\NThe willingness then to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.58,0:43:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,how the world works.\NThey don't get into indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.58,0:43:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the IRS has its way\Nof being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.58,0:43:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They get out of right and wrong.\NThey just accept that's how it is in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.58,0:43:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they go with it.\NSo, the beginning of transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.58,0:43:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness then\Nis the real realization
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.58,0:43:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the source\Nand therefore the world begins to look
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.58,0:43:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,harmonious and merciful.\NThat empowerment moves a person up then
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.16,0:43:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next energy field of love.\NWhat do we mean by love?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.16,0:43:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't mean the sentimental emotionalism\Nthat comes out of the solar plexus attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.16,0:43:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Hollywood calls love.\NThat emotionalism
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.16,0:43:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of a possessive ownership\Nof the other person
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.16,0:43:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and that back and forth control.\NThe subtle power struggles
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.16,0:44:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that go on.\NThat enamored coming out of a song
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.16,0:44:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you leave me I'll die kind of thing.\NIf you leave me I will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.32,0:44:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all coming out of an attachment\Nwhich has nothing to do with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.32,0:44:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about here unconditional love.\NA way of being with life
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.32,0:44:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that nurtures, supports\Nwhich is of its own nature forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.32,0:44:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the beginning of the revelation\Nof some of the truth of life
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.32,0:44:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because within the brain\Nthere's the release of endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.32,0:44:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Endorphins allow\Na certain inner state
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.32,0:44:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to occur, a way of being with oneself\Nand one's body and the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.32,0:44:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the world\Nstarts to appear loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.32,0:44:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that person walks down the street\Nfeeling somewhat mellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.32,0:44:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They see the lovingness\Nthat really goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.32,0:44:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath the apparent trivialities\Nthey really see the lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.32,0:44:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that holds all of mankind together.\NThey're moving into a higher energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.32,0:44:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing life as harmonious\Nseeing life as loving
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.86,0:45:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see how much stress now\Nthis person is vulnerable to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.86,0:45:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are coming\Nfrom a forgivingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.86,0:45:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That forgivingness\Nthe coming out of the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.41,0:45:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of that feel which you choose for yourself\Nwe call it lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.41,0:45:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the person\Ncoming out of lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.41,0:45:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is loving towards all things\Nat all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.41,0:45:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Loving towards mankind.\NLoving and nurturing towards oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.41,0:45:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the difference\Nin how these people would view themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.41,0:45:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The harshness\Nof the perfectionist
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.41,0:45:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,puts him always at stress\Nwith his own human nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.41,0:45:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The unforgivingness\Nthe capacity to judge and condemn
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.41,0:45:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the self-hatred and guilt\Nmeans for that person
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.41,0:45:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to breathe in and out\Nis to be in a state of stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.41,0:45:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If he gets up late\Nhe blames himself for getting up late.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.41,0:45:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The stress is there\Ncoming out of the perfectionism
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.41,0:46:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the inflexibility\Nthe capacity for self-condemnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.41,0:46:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the stress you see\Nis internally generated.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.41,0:46:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The open-minded person\Nthat starts to become more easy with himself
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.41,0:46:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to become accepting\Nof his own humaneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.41,0:46:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we move up to forgiveness\Nwe have that mental attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.41,0:46:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of the readiness\Nto allow the humaneness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.41,0:46:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we do that\Nwe allow our own humaneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.92,0:46:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We move up then\Nto an even higher energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.92,0:46:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of joyfulness\Nwhich is approaching the beginning awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.92,0:46:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the reality of that\Nin which you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.92,0:46:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That you are not the experience\Nyou are the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.92,0:46:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not at the effect of the world\Nyou are the one that is determining
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.92,0:46:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you experience it.\NAnd so you develop a certain inner serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.92,0:46:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of this\Npassion towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.92,0:46:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning to see the incredible\Nbeauty and perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.92,0:47:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencing of the oneness\Nand the unity of all life.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.92,0:47:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that one\Nso that person opens the newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.92,0:47:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you see and experiences\Nthe totality of man's lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.92,0:47:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing that despite\Nhis humaneness which is what is making
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.92,0:47:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all the articles appear\Nin the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.92,0:47:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of that onward movement\Nthe expression of the onward movement
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.92,0:47:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and evolution of man's consciousness.\NAnd so when that person walks down
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.24,0:47:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the same street\Nhe experiences only
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.24,0:47:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible beauty of it.\NExperiencing the beauty of life
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.24,0:47:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in all its magnificent expression.\NAs though you see
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.24,0:47:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose in the middle of its unfoldingness.\NSee the perfectionist
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.24,0:47:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,would look at the half unfolded rose\Nand say I don't want that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.24,0:47:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an imperfect rose.\NThe person on this level
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.75,0:47:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,sees the perfection of the evolution of life\Nitself and sees all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.75,0:47:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as that half unfolded rose.\NThat in one second
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.75,0:48:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only a cross section\Nbut projects forward in time
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.75,0:48:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees the unfoldingness\Nand the incredible beauty and precision
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes aware\Ninwardly of the inner sacredness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of all life.\NIt's obvious then as we talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.90,0:48:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,these energy fields\Nas these levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.90,0:48:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are determining\Nhow we experience life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.90,0:48:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They are determining\Nwhat kind of a God we think
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.90,0:48:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exists in the universe.\NThese energy fields are determining
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.90,0:48:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of emotions\Nwhich we are expressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.90,0:48:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this expressing\Na process going on
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.90,0:48:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness itself.\NIt certainly is very clear to us now
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.03,0:48:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is nothing\Nout there
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.03,0:48:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that has the power\Nto create stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.03,0:48:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That we ourselves\Nare the creators of stress
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.03,0:49:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by the positions\Nby our attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.16,0:49:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that the open minded\Neasy going person
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.16,0:49:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't experience stress\Nwhen somebody backs into his fender
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.18,0:49:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the parking lot.\NWhat happens, you've experienced it yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.18,0:49:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in a good mood.\NYou see what is stressful in one mood
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.18,0:49:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is not stressful in another.\NAnd so I came out myself
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.44,0:49:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,one day to the parking lot\Nand there was somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.57,0:49:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the only offender.\NAnd the person was very upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.57,0:49:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly my only concern\Nwas the upsetness of this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.57,0:49:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kept telling them\Nthere's nothing to be upset about.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.57,0:49:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's only offender.\NWe both got insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.57,0:49:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no big deal.\NSo it's a little nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.76,0:49:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to take your car\Nto the body shop and get it fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.76,0:49:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's really no big deal.\NSo it was the getting
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:49:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the desire to heal that upset\Nthat arose in the field
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:50:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of my own consciousness.\NSo whether it's something
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.34,0:50:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that sends you into self pity\Nabout what an unjust world this is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.34,0:50:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that people back into your fender.\NWhether you want to punch the guy
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.34,0:50:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the nose because you've got\Nso much anger in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.34,0:50:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're concerned\Nin just handling the facts involved
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.34,0:50:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with no particular feeling.\NThe detached person would just handle
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.53,0:50:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this with no particular feeling.\NThey just want to support life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.53,0:50:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and relieve their anxiety and their fear.\NAll of that you see is coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.53,0:50:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of who you are.\NIt doesn't exist in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.53,0:50:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A dented fender therefore has no power\Nover your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.53,0:50:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've just taken its power away.\NWe've just owned it back within ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.53,0:50:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've just precluded\Nthe sources of stress
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.53,0:50:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by just the realization\Nabout what we've talked about thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.53,0:50:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain state of inner peace then\Nautomatically comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.53,0:50:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of our willingness to give up\Ncertain positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.53,0:51:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our willingness to give up judging others.\NMaking them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.53,0:51:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our willingness then to come from\Na forgiving understanding position.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.53,0:51:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, right or wrong\Ndoesn't really solve anything, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.53,0:51:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to accept people\Nas they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.53,0:51:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If we come from this position here\Nmaking them wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.53,0:51:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we live in a world of win-lose.\NThe people at the bottom here
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.53,0:51:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from a world\Nof lose-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.53,0:51:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a world where I lose\Nand the company loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.53,0:51:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the\Nenergy field here
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.53,0:51:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we come from positions\Nwhich result in
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.53,0:51:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,win-lose.\NIt means if I win, you lose, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.88,0:51:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stressful\Nby the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.88,0:51:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stressful in the very way\Nthat it's set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.88,0:51:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even if you win\Nyou have to go through the anxiety of losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.88,0:51:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So even winning doesn't win.\NEven winning doesn't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.88,0:52:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that people, for instance,\Nwho say, I want to have a lot of money
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.07,0:52:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens to them\Nwhen you give them a lot of money?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.07,0:52:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some interesting research has been done\Non people who win
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.07,0:52:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of dollars\Nin big lotteries and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.07,0:52:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We find out that within five years\Na five-year follow-up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.07,0:52:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the degree of happiness in this group of people\Nwas dismal.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.07,0:52:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The suicide rate,\Nthe divorce rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.07,0:52:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the sickness rate,\Nthe addiction to drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.26,0:52:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,had risen spectacularly in these people\Nwho had gotten ostensibly
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.26,0:52:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the very thing they wanted.\NThe reason they played the lottery
