Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.84,1:10:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,spend the rest of their life battling that which they have projected out there.\NSo the comedy of it all, that's the basis of all humor, you know, laughing at those
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.09,1:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities of life, holding them from a position which exposes the paradox.\NBecause humor is seeing the paradox, the funniness of it, the humor of it, to hold lightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to become at the effect then of anything out there whatsoever.\NIt's we ourselves who determine by our attitudes, by our position, whether life is experienced
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.42,1:10:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as joyful and harmonious, easygoing, or whether we experience it as our enemy.\NThe willingness to go with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.59,1:10:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go with it.\NWe begin to admire people who are capable and easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.07,1:11:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the objection comes up, well, the easygoing person, aren't they a pushover,\Nyou know, in business?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.86,1:11:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The misunderstanding of what easygoingness means.\NNo, easygoing means acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.16,1:11:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to be adequate.\NIf you can see the humor of life, if you feel adequate and solid within yourself, if you
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.88,1:11:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you're the source of how you experience life.\NThen you can handle those things which the world considers difficult with ease.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.90,1:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be the boss, and if the janitor doesn't show up, it doesn't bother you at all.\NWhen the business closes for the day, you take off your coat, roll up your sleeves, and
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.92,1:11:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you sweep it out.\NIt doesn't make any difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.11,1:11:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause that which I am is unaffected by all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.76,1:11:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is that I am that which experiences experience.\NThe realization that I am the experiencer of experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.66,1:11:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That that's where I live.\NI live within my consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.78,1:11:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference.\NWhether I surround myself with appurtenances that look important, or whether I roll up
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.68,1:12:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,my sleeves and I sweep out the office myself, that which I am is totally unaffected.\NThat which I am is just enjoying the experience of its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.12,1:12:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoying one's own inner aliveness.\NStress just doesn't exist in that kind of a position about the world, where we clearly
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.84,1:12:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,identify who we really are.\NWhen we stop identifying with the body as being who we are, we pointed out right in the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.78,1:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,very beginning, the body is half a dozen times removed from the reality of who we are.\NWhen we stop identifying with the events out there, when we stop giving them power over
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.90,1:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,our life, then comes an inner serenity.\NYou know, it's like the solar plexus can relax at last.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.12,1:12:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're out of danger.\NWe're out of danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.84,1:12:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've sort of transcended the world.\NWe've learned what the source of stress is.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.32,1:13:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just knowing what the source of stress is already makes us immune to it, already moves\Nus into a different way of being with life, allows us to see it as our own creation.
